title: What Driverless Waymo Taxi Rides Are Like in San Francisco
description: On Monday, Waymo began letting the public pay for rides in its driverless cars in San Francisco. The New York Times dispatched three reporters around the city to test the service.

title: Arm, the Chip Designer, Files for an I.P.O. Expected to Be Among the Largest
description: The I.P.O. filing means Arm can begin to gauge investor interest, which will be critical to the share sale.

title: More Screen Time Delays Development in Babies, Study Finds
description: One-year-olds exposed to more than four hours of screen time a day experienced developmental delays in communication and problem-solving skills at ages 2 and 4, according to a new study

title: How Nvidia Built a Competitive Moat Around A.I. Chips
description: The most visible winner of the artificial intelligence boom achieved its dominance by becoming a one-stop shop for A.I. development, from chips to software to other services.
